59th Templar ( God I wish I could request to keep the templar title at 60 ) of Divine Grace <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujexielia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jexielia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 834<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/20/02 9:58:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Peridots</span><hr size=1> As a cleric I find that there are usually 2 types of groups I run into 1.  Those who over compensate their clerics and 2.  Those who dont compensate at all.<br>
<br>
I find myself in the position where I am offered to much cash loot and I respond by saying that the dots have been covered and that if the group continues on for some time I'll speak up when I feel that another item might be necessary.<br>
<br>
One thing I know is that there is a big difference in cash loot for different zones/camps.  In Velks I find that there are often no cash loot drops unless you're at a good camp spot.  In this circumstance I'll often cast Pinzarn on everyone but the main tanks (Pinzarn uses jaspers instead of peridots if ya dont know) so it still costs but its not as much of a loss.  Perhaps some will argue that this is innapropriate but I have yet to have anyone complain.<br>
<br>
As a cleric I also know what a profit can be made by stopping for a few moments (inbetween groups) to res people making donations... this helps cover the expenses of groups that DONT contribute or cant contribute as much as it costs.  If Im in a group in such a zone as KC and I get a tell saying "hey can you res me, I'll donate" generally I try to say "no sorry I have to reserve my mana for heals" ~ if group hasnt been able to compensate for costs occasionally I'll say "sure might be a minute I'll need to make sure I have the mana" and then inform the group "hey going to res this guy to help cover dot costs" ~ normally its not a problem.  God knows how much clerics can make taking the time to res someone.  Nothing imho is smarter than taking time to res and accepting the donations to help cover the expense of being a cleric.  <br>
<br>
It seems unfair to me at times for group members to have to sacrifice so much for clerics who seek more compensation than they need when they are, in fact, not the only ones who have costs.  (tanks with shrink potions for some zones, chanters with dots, wizards with TL componants, arrows for the puller, etc... yeah some are minor but they are there)<br>
<br>
When Im not playing a cleric I tend to have dots handy... usually for paying for res's because as a cleric I love being payed with dots for res's and I know others do too.  And sometimes in groups I find that others usually keep dots handy... and many will see that no cash loot is being given and they'll hand me 2-3 dots for the symbols I've casted on them... its something that always impresses me.<br>
<br>
One thing I do see a lot of, which disappoints me, are clerics who dont have dots.  I never carry less than 8 stacks of peridots and 5 stacks of jaspers.  When a group doesnt compensate or if the drops arent plentiful its just something you have to eat up.  There's no reason for a cleric NOT to dot their group, if the group is shitty about costs or is just downright neglectful, find another group or speak up and say "hey dots cost X amount, anyone mind if I get a few of the cash drops to compensate" ~ they wont say no.<br>
<br>
Another thing is that if a cleric says "dots cost so much bla bla bla" it sometimes makes me a bit bitter when they overprice them... there is no reason why a cleric cant invest in a few + cha items allowing them to buy dots at a somewhat reasonable price.  I never pay more than 10.5 pp per dot... there's no reason to.  I just switch my +cha gear when Im buying/selling and then carry on.  No cleric should say they cost much more than that imho.<br>
<br>
Anyway... those are my thoughts.<br>
